      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A rhythmic, piercing squeal that happens consistently while moving suggests something is actively rubbing or vibrating. It could be that a clip, like a caliper slide pin or anti-rattle clip, wasn't fully seated or is slightly misaligned. Sometimes, even a tiny speck of grime or metal dust, if it gets wedged, can cause this noise. It would be best to visually inspect the caliper bracket area for any foreign objects or improper seating of the components.",
      "source": "target",
