      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That unsettling, shrill noise might be related to the rotor itself, perhaps a slight runout or unevenness, which can be amplified by the new pads. It could also possibly be a slight warp or rocking motion within the caliper piston or guide pins, though these are harder to spot without specialized tools. If you can safely coat the caliper slide pins lightly with silicone grease, it might resolve any mild binding causing the squeal. If the sound continues, a shop expert should examine the pads and rotors on a lift.",
      "source": "target",
